<title>USA: RSL Communications Ltd Q1 net loss widens.</title>
<headline>RSL Communications Ltd Q1 net loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three Months Ended</p>
<p>					    Mar 31, 1997   Mar 31, 1996</p>
<p> REVENUES					$42,168	  $15,864</p>
<p> INTEREST INCOME				 3,792		 58</p>
<p> INTEREST EXPENSE			    (9,431)	    (298)</p>
<p> OTHER EXPENSE				   (255)		 --</p>
<p> MINORITY INTEREST			     (119)		 --</p>
<p> INCOME TAXES				    (258)		 --</p>
<p> NET LOSS				     (19,147)	  (4,790)</p>
<p> LOSS PER SHARE OF CLASS B COMMON STOCK (3.98)	   (1.64)</p>
<p>WEIGHTED AVERAGE NUMBER OF SHARES OF</p>
<p>  CLASS B COMMON STOCK OUTSTANDING	 4,808	    2,928</p>
<p>				(in thousands, except loss per share)</p>
<p>NOTE:  The company said increased U.S. revenues resulted from increased traffic volume from existing customers and significant increases in its end user customer base. European revenues increased as a result of the commencement of revenues at start-up operations in the U.K., Sweden and Finland and growth from operations acquired in Germany, France and the Netherlands.</p>
